This paper deals with lossy coding of perceptually relevant signals, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of quantization, which is a common technique in multimedia processing (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the preservation of distribution, which is a topic in statistical learning (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG).
